issue.title: Do we have precise dates for each annotation?
issue.body:
I am trying to recover the annotations so that I can train on other images.
I see that the coordinates are in the folder '[data_coordinates](https://github.com/yzyly1992/GloSoFarID/tree/main/data_coordinates)' .
How about the dates? Are there somewhere? I see the year in the filenames but do we have a precise date for the annotations?

comment.body:
> I am trying to recover the annotations so that I can train on other images. I see that the coordinates are in the folder '[data_coordinates](https://github.com/yzyly1992/GloSoFarID/tree/main/data_coordinates)' . How about the dates? Are there somewhere? I see the year in the filenames but do we have a precise date for the annotations?

No precise date since we are taking median value:
```
def get_input_image(year: int, default_value: float = 1000.0) -> ee.Image:
    return (
        ee.ImageCollection("COPERNICUS/S2_HARMONIZED")  # Sentinel-2 images
        .filterDate(f"{year}-1-1", f"{year}-12-31")  # filter by year
        .filter(ee.Filter.lt("CLOUDY_PIXEL_PERCENTAGE", 20))  # filter cloudy images
        .map(mask_sentinel2_clouds)  # mask/hide cloudy pixels
        .select("B.*")  # select all bands starting with B
        .median()  # median of all non-cloudy pixels
        .unmask(default_value)  # default value for masked pixels
        .float()  # convert to float32
    )
```

commits.message: integration tests for all post endpoints

Update security policies and improve subscription error handling

- Enhanced Content Security Policy to include additional domains for script and frame sources.
- Updated Google AdSense script integration to use environment variable for client ID.
- Improved error handling in subscription creation process, including user validation and Stripe customer retrieval.
- Added specific error messages and redirection logic for better user experience during subscription failures.
Merge branch 'Stripe-payment-for-MVP' of https://github.com/Cburgos7/DateThinker into Stripe-payment-for-MVP

Refactor subscription handling and improve error management

- Reintroduced @supabase/ssr in both package.json and package-lock.json for better SSR support.
- Enhanced error handling in subscription creation functions to provide clearer feedback and redirection for users.
- Updated direct checkout API to handle email and type parameters more effectively, ensuring proper customer creation and session management.
- Simplified the PricingPage component by utilizing auth context for user management and improving loading states.
- Added direct checkout links for both monthly and lifetime subscriptions to enhance user experience.

Refactor Next.js configuration and enhance API routes

- Cleaned up the Next.js configuration by removing unnecessary settings and optimizing build performance.
- Updated security headers to retain only essential ones for improved security.
- Marked multiple API routes as dynamic to handle cookie usage correctly.
- Improved error handling and response structure in various API routes, including Stripe status checks and Google Places API debugging.
- Removed deprecated build commands and streamlined the Vercel configuration for better deployment practices.

Update dependencies and enhance checkout button redirect logic

- Added @supabase/ssr to package.json and package-lock.json for improved server-side rendering support.
- Changed the version specification for the Next.js dependency to allow for minor updates.
- Improved the redirect logic in the CheckoutButton component to use window.location.assign for better reliability, with a fallback mechanism in case of failure.

Enhance Next.js configuration and improve API cookie handling

- Updated next.config.js to enable CSS optimization, React strict mode, and SWC minification for better performance.
- Removed @supabase/ssr from package.json to streamline dependencies.
- Improved cookie handling in the subscription status API route for more robust session management.
